recipe for cheesecake i like baking and want to try a recipe for cheesecake i have already made chocolate swirl and ny cheesecakes this cheesecake recipe is amazing it is white chocolate raspberry for the crust cup slivered almonds cups graham cracker crumbs ounces stick cup unsalted butter melted for filling ounces fine quality white chocolate ounce packages cream cheese softened cup plus tablespoons sugar whole large eggs large egg yolks tablespoons all purpose flour teaspoon vanilla cups fresh raspberries ounces fresh raspberries for garnish make crust finely grind almonds and crumbs in a food processor and add butter blending until combined press over bottom and up side of a inch springform pan make filling preheat oven to degrees melt chocolate in double boiler or a large metal bowl set over a saucepan of barely simmering water stirring until smooth and remove from heat beat cream cheese with an electric mixer at medium speed until fluffy then beat in sugar add whole eggs and yolks at a time beating well at low speed and scraping down bowl after each addition beat in flour and vanilla until just combined then add melted chocolate in a slow stream beating until filling is well combined arrange berries in layer over crust and pour filling into crust bake in the middle of the oven until cake is set inches from edge but center is still wobbly when pan is gently shaken to minutes run a thin knife around edge of cake to loosen then cool completely in pan on a rack cake will continue to set as it cools serve at room temperature or chilled i also have a recipe that is for lemon cheesecake bars not a cake but soooo delicious cups graham cracker crumbs cup chopped pecans cup sugar cup butter melted ounces cream cheese softened ounce can sweetened condensed milk cup fresh lemon juice large eggs teaspoon vanilla preheat oven to combine graham cracker crumbs pecans sugar and melted butter mix well reserve cup crumb mixture press the rest into a x baking pan bake for minutes allow to cool while the crust is cooling beat cream cheese until it's fluffy gradually beat in the milk add eggs until mixture is just combined stir in the lemon juice and vanilla pour mixture into prepared crust sprinkle the reserved crumb mixture over the top of the cheesecake layer bake for about minutes cool for about an hour then cut into bars store in your refrigerator Puff pastry Baked Alaska Brewery Butter Milk Kit Kat Dim sum In-N-Out Burger German cuisine French fries Vinegar Flour Idli Bacon French toast Cooking weights and measures Martini cocktail Casting Pop-Tarts Muesli Horehound Custard Bengali cuisine Kraft Dinner Baklava Soft drink D__ner kebab Milkshake Hamburger Cajun cuisine Chicken soup Peanut butter Sugarcane Plastic Pottery Steel Wine Mooncake Rum Refrigerator Paint Haggis Yerba mate Kosher foods Yoplait Sushi Turkish Delight Oreo Cuisine of Argentina Cuisine of the Southern United States Gatorade Paneer B__chamel sauce Cooking Tortilla Roast beef Turkish coffee Wine making Cuisine of Singapore Cuisine of Malaysia Cider Champagne (beverage) Welding Thermal power station 